    "It is worthwhile to notice that using LLMs to generate training data has become a common practice proven to be effective and widely adopted by related literature [4,7].",
    "To verify the data quality, we invited five domain experts with graduated degree in urban planning to judge the generated instruction pairs, comparing different approaches.",
    "Specifically, we sample 100 instruction pairs generated by different approaches, and asked the domain experts to score the generated data from the perspective of both correctiveness and informativeness.",
    "The results are demonstrated in Table 4.",
    "ResultsWe leveraged our constructed UrbanPlanText dataset to fine-tune LLMs using LLaMA-Factory [45]."
